Description: Heavily corroded copper alloy round stud in the shape of an hemispherical button, the round part of it being welded to a round disc with grooved edge. In the middle of the underside remains part of a narrow shank, of rectangular cross-section.
Curator's comments: One of the "nail-heads of all forms, flat, round, massive parabolic, pyramidal, rosette and concentric circles" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.80, p.186, pl.28)
